## Frontend Tests (Jest + React Testing Library)

### Component Test Pattern

ALWAYS include an accessibility scan with jest-axe:

```typescript
import { render, screen } from "@testing-library/react";
import { axe } from "jest-axe";
import { MyComponent } from "src/components/domain/MyComponent";

describe("MyComponent", () => {
  it("renders without errors", () => {
    const { container } = render(<MyComponent />);
    expect(screen.getByText("Expected text")).toBeInTheDocument();
  });

  it("passes accessibility scan", async () => {
    const { container } = render(<MyComponent />);
    const results = await axe(container);
    expect(results).toHaveNoViolations();
  });
});
```

### Hook Test Pattern

```typescript
import { renderHook, act } from "@testing-library/react";
import { useMyHook } from "src/hooks/useMyHook";

describe("useMyHook", () => {
  it("returns expected initial state", () => {
    const { result } = renderHook(() => useMyHook());
    expect(result.current.value).toBe(expectedValue);
  });
});
```

### Mock Patterns

- Mock API calls with `jest.mock("src/services/fetch")`
- Mock `next/navigation` for router-dependent components
- Mock `next-intl` for i18n-dependent components
- NEVER mock implementation details — test behavior

### E2E Tests (Playwright)

```typescript
import { test, expect } from "@playwright/test";

test("<feature> — <scenario>", async ({ page }) => {
  await page.goto("/path");
  await expect(page.getByRole("heading", { name: "Title" })).toBeVisible();
});
```

- Playwright tests live in `frontend/e2e/`
- Use 4 shards for parallel execution
- Use blob report merging for CI

## Quality Gate Pipeline

After generating tests, run the following specialist validation passes.

### Gate 1: Convention Compliance (mandatory)
Invoke `codebase-conventions-reviewer` to validate all generated tests against project testing conventions.
- Check: factory usage (`.build()` vs `.create()`), test structure, naming conventions, fixture patterns, mock patterns
- If violations found: fix them before proceeding

### Gate 2: Test Efficiency (mandatory)
Invoke `performance-oracle` to validate test performance patterns.
- Check: unnecessary `Factory.create()` where `.build()` suffices, redundant DB operations, missing parametrize for input variations, proper fixture scoping
- If issues found: fix before proceeding

### Gate 3: Language Quality (mandatory)
Invoke `kieran-python-reviewer` (for pytest) or `kieran-typescript-reviewer` (for Jest/Playwright) for language-specific quality.
- Check: idiomatic test patterns, assertion quality, edge case coverage, type safety in mocks
- If issues found: fix before proceeding

### Gate 4: Data Integrity (conditional)
If tests involve `Factory.create()` or database operations, invoke `data-integrity-guardian`.
- Check: proper `enable_factory_create` fixture usage, no manual `db_session.commit()`, transaction isolation
- If issues found: fix before presenting final output

## Test Coverage Checklist

- [ ] Success path (happy path)
- [ ] Error/not-found path
- [ ] Validation error path (422)
- [ ] Auth failure path (401/403) if endpoint requires auth
- [ ] Accessibility scan (frontend components)
- [ ] Factory uses `.build()` where possible, `.create()` only when DB needed
